  </tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#13273C">Posted By: <a href="mailto:neilmc@intertex.net">Skalz Mobseeker</a> of Torvonnilous on Nov. 30, 2000 at 5:30pm EST</td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#183049">I came back after a few levels to get some more Iksar blood (and a Burynai Legion Gi!).  Well I got a new drop off most, but not all Burynai slaves; niccolite.  It's No Drop, but stacks and looks like a rock of some kind.  Anyone know what it's for?  Also I got a Drogan Obsidian Dagger here off a whipcracker when the server repopped after a patch.<br><br></td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#13273C">Posted By: <a href="mailto:skandrannon@msn.com">Stormin Skyblaze</a> of The Seventh Hammer on Nov. 20, 2000 at 1:24pm EST</td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#183049">This is a good zone in IMHO.  The lack of most money, and the rarity of the drops are made up for my the rather common dropping of other things.  For example, I was there last night for only 45mins tops, and I picked up a black pearl, two peridots, an emerald, some blue stuff called Mt. death mineral salts, iksar blood, and other various GEMS.  It seems to me Verant did a GOOD job on this zone, they are in a mine, right?  Well then how would they get out and get money, instead the have gems that sell for a bit of pp!  Good Job verant, i'll be here till they are all green and i have all the loot out of this place :)  Nice drops too, have you seen that shield!<br><br></td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#13273C">Posted By: <a href="mailto:jfbii@hotmail.com">Snarfo</a> of Prexus on Nov. 15, 2000 at 9:32am EST</td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#183049">The sleeping ogre for monk epic quest turns into "trunt", lvl 59 I believe, after he is giving the necessary item. He is gullerback on steroids. He has a high magic resistance and when you get him down to low health he becomes enraged.<br>
<br>
Also, the sleeping ogre has a large aggro range, so don't engage him till your ready. And one last note, if you pull him, keep a eye, get as clost to him as you can to pull him, if you lose him he wanders off and suicides himself to prevent being pulled to zone. Spawn time is 3 hours if he suicides or you kill him.<br><br></td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#13273C">Posted By: <a href="mailto:xbiggio7x@aol.com">Udyo Steelfoot</a> of tarew marr on Nov. 08, 2000 at 4:03pm EST</td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#183049">one word for this zone WOW.  this has got to be some of the best exp ever. This place can easily be done with a group of 3 near lvl 40.  Chanter Cleric Warrior, or druid instead of cleric.  Minimal healing is needed if you use stun fighting. My group went on the burynai side and went through ever last one.  I ended up with 3/4 bubs of exp, and thats in lvl 40.  The other two people got  over a bub and a half of exp.  Just grab a map and move through areas as quickly as possible, resting safely in hallways.  Onle things that see through invis are spiders but they can be avoided by hugging walls. <br><br></td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#13273C">Posted By: <a href="mailto:gamstr@aol.com">KrissK</a> of Bristlebane on Nov. 05, 2000 at 2:42am EST</td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#183049">I agree with Skalz.  Tonight my group got one of the Drogan Obsidian Dagger's to drop from a regular whipcracker goblin in Nurga.  Our Warrior was quite happy :)<br><br></td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#13273C">Posted By: <a href="mailto:neilmc@intertex.net">Skalz Mobseeker</a> of Torvonnilous on Oct. 30, 2000 at 10:00am EST</td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#183049">After killing many, many goblins I got some goblin forged iron boots (7ac +10hps -2fr, wt. 7.5 not magic) to drop off a goblin backbiter.  So my guess would be that very, very rarely you can get a random item from Droga, in Nurga.  I don't know, maybe these items are this rare in Droga too.  Anyway, good luck.<br><br></td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#13273C">Posted By: <a href="mailto:mklein@keanesea.com">Stronghand_VZ</a> of VallonZek on Oct. 23, 2000 at 5:38pm EST</td></tr>
